A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Judge John Allen; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Judge John Allen, a native of Columbus, Georgia; decorated fighter pilot;
4 and exemplary member of the judiciary; and
5 WHEREAS, Judge John Allen served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and liberty with
6 the United States Air Force and was honorably discharged from service as a captain in 1973,
7 earning six Distinguished Flying Crosses and 23 Air Medals; and
8 WHEREAS, after his military service, he pursued legal education at the University of Florida
9 and returned to Columbus in 1976 to begin his distinguished career in law, later serving as
10 a judge in the Recorder's Court, State Court, and Superior Court of Muscogee County for a
11 combined 26 years; and
12 WHEREAS, a trailblazer for civil rights, Judge John Allen marched in Selma for voting
13 rights in 1965, and in the 1970s, he co-founded the first integrated law firm in Columbus,
14 paving the way for greater representation and equality in the legal profession; and
