15 WHEREAS, he served as the chief judge of the Chattahoochee Judicial Circuit upon his
16 retirement in 2013 and was inducted into the Georgia Military Veterans Hall of Fame in 2020
17 in recognition of his outstanding service to both his country and his community; and
18 WHEREAS, his legacy of leadership extended beyond the courtroom through his
19 involvement in numerous community organizations, including the Columbus Airport
20 Commission, the Columbus High School Vocational Education Advisory Board, the Urban
21 League Board of Directors, the Area Ten Special Olympics Advisory Board, and the African
22 American Historic Preservation Society; and
23 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
24 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
25 made this world a better place in which to live; and
26 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Judge John Allen will long be remembered
27 for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who had the great
28 fortune of knowing him.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Judge John Allen and
31 express their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 family of Judge John Allen.
